  <title translate="true">Tip #56</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Modifying the instance variables of a class can make old binary (STB) filed instances of the class become incompatible so that they will refuse to load in future.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This incompatibility can be rectified by supplying an appropriate class side </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">#stbConvertFrom</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">: method for the class whose shape has been changed. This tells the STB loader how to map old instances to the new format.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
